  "output": "Good picture now. No frontend or DB yet ŌĆö pure Python core. Analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Performance Analysis: Core Engine (Sprint 1)\n\n**No React, no DB yet** ŌĆö skipping N+1 queries and re-renders. Findings are engine-only.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Memory Leak ŌĆö `incoming_orders` grows unbounded\n\n`order_processor.py:72` appends to `upstream_ps.incoming_orders` every round. Nothing ever clears it. Over 26 rounds each player accumulates the full order history.\n\n```python\n# current ŌĆö leaks\nupstream_ps.incoming_orders.append(order_qty)\n\n# fix ŌĆö clear at round start in process_round, or just pop:\norder_qty = upstream_ps.incoming_orders.pop(0) if upstream_ps.incoming_orders else 0\n```\n\nThis also affects serialized game state size ŌĆö relevant once GameState persists to PostgreSQL.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Double-Pass in `advance_shipments`\n\n`order_processor.py:7ŌĆō13` iterates `incoming_shipments` twice ŌĆö once to sum arrivals, once to rebuild the list.\n\n```python\n# current: 2 passes\narrived = sum(s.quantity for s in ps.incoming_shipments if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1)\nps.incoming_shipments = [IncomingShipment(...) for s in ps.incoming_shipments if s.arrives_in_rounds > 1]\n\n# fix: 1 pass\narrived = 0\nremaining = []\nfor s in ps.incoming_shipments:\n    if s.arrives_in_rounds == 1:\n        arrived += s.quantity\n    else:\n        remaining.append(IncomingShipment(quantity=s.quantity, arrives_in_rounds=s.arrives_in_rounds - 1))\nps.incoming_shipments = remaining\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Redundant Pydantic Object Construction Each Round\n\nSame `advance_shipments` list comprehension creates new `IncomingShipment` Pydantic v2 instances for every non-arrived shipment. Pydantic v2 runs validators on each construction. With `shipping_delay=2`, 4 players, 26 rounds ŌåÆ ~200+ avoidable model constructions.\n\n`IncomingShipment` only has two int fields. Use a plain dataclass or `__slots__`-based class:\n\n```python\n# core/models/order.py ŌĆö swap to dataclass\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass(slots=True)\nclass IncomingShipment:\n    quantity: int\n    arrives_in_rounds: int\n```\n\nThen mutate in-place instead of reconstructing:\n```python\ns.arrives_in_rounds -= 1\n```\n\nIf Pydantic validation on this model is needed for API serialization, keep the Pydantic model but add a separate internal `_ShipmentSlot` for the hot path.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `OrderUpToAI` Recomputes Pipeline Every Decision\n\n`rule_based.py:16` sums all incoming shipments fresh each call. With 4 AI players per round, 26 rounds = 104 redundant sums.\n\n```python\n# current\npipeline = sum(s.quantity for s in ps.incoming_shipments)\n\n# option: track pipeline_stock as a field on PlayerState\n# increment on append, decrement on arrival in advance_shipments\n```\n\nAdds one int field to `PlayerState`; eliminates the sum entirely.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Correctness Bug Masquerading as Performance\n\n`game.py:42` ŌĆö `PlayerState.round_cost()` hardcodes module-level constants:\n\n```python\ndef round_cost(self) -> float:\n    return self.inventory * HOLDING_COST_PER_UNIT + self.backlog * BACKLOG_COST_PER_UNIT\n```\n\nBut `accrue_costs` uses `state.config.holding_cost` / `state.config.backlog_cost`. Custom `GameConfig` costs diverge silently. Fix: remove `round_cost()` or accept `config` as a parameter.\n\n---\n\n### Priority Order\n\n| Issue | Impact | Effort |\n|---|---|---|\n| `incoming_orders` unbounded | High (memory + DB size) | Low |\n| `round_cost()` uses wrong constants | Medium (correctness) | Trivial |\n| Double-pass `advance_shipments` | Low now, scales with pipeline depth | Low |\n| Pydantic construction overhead | Low now, hot path at scale | Medium |\n| `pipeline` recompute in AI | Negligible at 4 players | Low |\n\nWant me to apply any of these?\n",
